flavor_text: This PokÃ©mon can easily melt holes in hard rocks with a liquid secreted from its mouth.

name: crustle
flavor_text: Competing for territory, Crustle fight viciously. The one whose boulder is broken is the loser of the battle.

name: scraggy
flavor_text: Its skin has a rubbery elasticity, so it can reduce damage by defensively pulling its skin up to its neck.

name: scrafty
flavor_text: Groups of them beat up anything that enters their territory. Each can spit acidic liquid from its mouth.

name: sigilyph
flavor_text: They never vary the route they fly, because their memories of guarding an ancient city remain steadfast.

name: yamask
flavor_text: Each of them carries a mask that used to be its face when it was human. Sometimes they look at it and cry.

name: cofagrigus
flavor_text: It has been said that they swallow those who get too close and turn them into mummies. They like to eat gold nuggets.

name: tirtouga
flavor_text: Restored from a fossil, this PokÃ©mon can dive to depths beyond half a mile.

name: carracosta
flavor_text: They can live both in the ocean and on land. A slap from one of them is enough to open a hole in the bottom of a tanker.

name: archen
flavor_text: Said to be an ancestor of bird PokÃ©mon, they were unable to fly and moved about by hopping from one branch to another.

name: archeops
flavor_text: They are intelligent and will cooperate to catch prey. From the ground, they use a running start to take flight.

name: trubbish
flavor_text: Inhaling the gas they belch will make you sleep for a week. They prefer unsanitary places.

name: garbodor
flavor_text: It clenches opponents with its left arm and finishes them off with foul-smelling poison gas belched from its mouth.

name: zorua
flavor_text: It changes into the forms of others to surprise them. Apparently, it often transforms into a silent child.

name: zoroark
flavor_text: Bonds between these PokÃ©mon are very strong. It protects the safety of its pack by tricking its opponents.

name: minccino
flavor_text: They greet one another by rubbing each other with their tails, which are always kept well groomed and clean.

name: cinccino
flavor_text: Their white fur is coated in a special oil that makes it easy for them to deflect attacks.

name: gothita
flavor_text: Their ribbonlike feelers increase their psychic power. They are always staring at something.

name: gothorita
flavor_text: They use hypnosis to control people and PokÃ©mon. Tales of Gothorita leading people astray are told in every corner.

name: gothitelle
flavor_text: Starry skies thousands of light-years away are visible in the space distorted by their intense psychic power.

name: solosis
flavor_text: They drive away attackers by unleashing psychic power. They can use telepathy to talk with others.

name: duosion
flavor_text: Since they have two divided brains, at times they suddenly try to take two different actions at once.

name: reuniclus
flavor_text: When Reuniclus shake hands, a network forms between their brains, increasing their psychic power.

name: ducklett
flavor_text: These bird PokÃ©mon are excellent divers. They swim around in the water eating their favorite food--peat moss.

name: swanna
flavor_text: Swanna start to dance at dusk. The one dancing in the middle is the leader of the flock.

name: vanillite
flavor_text: The temperature of their breath is -58Â° F. They create snow crystals and make snow fall in the areas around them.

name: vanillish
flavor_text: Snowy mountains are this PokÃ©monâs habitat. During an ancient ice age, they moved to southern areas.

name: vanilluxe
flavor_text: Swallowing large amounts of water, they make snow clouds inside their bodies and attack their foes with violent blizzards.

name: deerling
flavor_text: The color and scent of their fur changes to match the mountain grass. When they sense hostility, they hide in the grass.

name: sawsbuck
flavor_text: They migrate according to the seasons. People can tell the season by looking at Sawsbuckâs horns.

name: emolga
flavor_text: The energy made in its cheeksâ electric pouches is stored inside its membrane and released while it is gliding.

name: karrablast
flavor_text: These mysterious PokÃ©mon evolve when they receive electrical stimulation while they are in the same place as Shelmet.

name: escavalier
flavor_text: They fly around at high speed, striking with their pointed spears. Even when in trouble, they face opponents bravely.

name: foongus
flavor_text: It lures people in with its PokÃ© Ball pattern, then releases poison spores. Why it resembles a PokÃ© Ball is unknown.

name: amoonguss
flavor_text: It lures prey close by dancing and waving its arm caps, which resemble PokÃ© Balls, in a swaying motion.

name: frillish
flavor_text: With its thin, veil-like arms wrapped around the body of its opponent, it sinks to the ocean floor.

name: jellicent
flavor_text: The fate of the ships and crew that wander into Jellicentâs habitat: all sunken, all lost, all vanished.

name: alomomola
flavor_text: The special membrane enveloping Alomomola has the ability to heal wounds.

name: joltik
flavor_text: Joltik that live in cities have learned a technique for sucking electricity from the outlets in houses.

name: galvantula
flavor_text: When attacked, they create an electric barrier by spitting out many electrically charged threads.

name: ferroseed
flavor_text: When threatened, it attacks by shooting a barrage of spikes, which gives it a chance to escape by rolling away.

name: ferrothorn
flavor_text: It fights by swinging around its three spiky feelers. A hit from these steel spikes can reduce a boulder to rubble.

name: klink
flavor_text: The two minigears that mesh together are predetermined. Each will rebound from other minigears without meshing.

name: klang
flavor_text: By changing the direction in which it rotates, it communicates its feelings to others. When angry, it rotates faster.

name: klinklang
flavor_text: The gear with the red core is rotated at high speed for a rapid energy charge.

name: tynamo
flavor_text: While one alone doesnât have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

name: eelektrik
flavor_text: They coil around foes and shock them with electricity-generating organs that seem simply to be circular patterns.

name: eelektross
flavor_text: They crawl out of the ocean using their arms. They will attack prey on shore and immediately drag it into the ocean.

name: elgyem
flavor_text: It uses its strong psychic power to squeeze its opponentâs brain, causing unendurable headaches.

name: beheeyem
flavor_text: It can manipulate an opponentâs memory. Apparently, it communicates by flashing its three different-colored fingers.

name: litwick
flavor_text: Litwick shines a light that absorbs the life energy of people and PokÃ©mon, which becomes the fuel that it burns.

name: lampent
flavor_text: This ominous PokÃ©mon is feared. Through cities it wanders, searching for the spirits of the fallen.

name: chandelure
flavor_text: It absorbs a spirit, which it then burns. By waving the flames on its arms, it puts its foes into a hypnotic trance.

name: axew
flavor_text: They use their tusks to crush the berries they eat. Repeated regrowth makes their tusks strong and sharp.

name: fraxure
flavor_text: Since a broken tusk will not grow back, they diligently sharpen their tusks on river rocks after theyâve been fighting.

name: haxorus
flavor_text: They are kind but can be relentless when defending territory. They challenge foes with tusks that can cut steel.

name: cubchoo
flavor_text: When it is not feeling well, its mucus gets watery and the power of its Ice-type moves decreases.

name: beartic
flavor_text: It can make its breath freeze at will. Very able in the water, it swims around in northern seas and catches prey.

name: cryogonal
flavor_text: When its body temperature goes up, it turns into steam and vanishes. When its temperature lowers, it returns to ice.

name: shelmet
flavor_text: When attacked, it defends itself by closing the lid of its shell. It can spit a sticky, poisonous liquid.

name: accelgor
flavor_text: When its body dries out, it weakens. So, to prevent dehydration, it wraps itself in many layers of thin membrane.

name: stunfisk
flavor_text: Its skin is very hard, so it is unhurt even if stepped on by sumo wrestlers. It smiles when transmitting electricity.

name: mienfoo
flavor_text: In fights, they dominate with onslaughts of flowing, continuous attacks. With their sharp claws, they cut enemies.

name: mienshao
flavor_text: It wields the fur on its arms like a whip. Its arm attacks come with such rapidity that they cannot even be seen.

name: druddigon
flavor_text: It warms its body by absorbing sunlight with its wings. When its body temperature falls, it can no longer move.

name: golett
flavor_text: The energy that burns inside it enables it to move, but no one has yet been able to identify this energy.

name: golurk
flavor_text: It flies across the sky at Mach speeds. Removing the seal on its chest makes its internal energy go out of control.

name: pawniard
flavor_text: Blades comprise this PokÃ©monâs entire body. If battling dulls the blades, it sharpens them on stones by the river.

name: bisharp
flavor_text: It leads a group of Pawniard. It battles to become the boss, but will be driven from the group if it loses.

name: bouffalant
flavor_text: Their fluffy fur absorbs damage, even if they strike foes with a fierce headbutt.

name: rufflet
flavor_text: They crush berries with their talons. They bravely stand up to any opponent, no matter how strong it is.

name: braviary
flavor_text: They fight for their friends without any thought about danger to themselves. One can carry a car while flying.

name: vullaby
flavor_text: Their wings are too tiny to allow them to fly. They guard their posteriors with bones that were gathered by Mandibuzz.

name: mandibuzz
flavor_text: It makes a nest out of bones it finds. It grabs weakened prey in its talons and hauls it to its nest of bones.

name: heatmor
flavor_text: It breathes through a hole in its tail while it burns with an internal fire. Durant is its prey.

name: durant
flavor_text: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

name: deino
flavor_text: It tends to bite everything, and it is not a picky eater. Approaching it carelessly is dangerous.

name: zweilous
flavor_text: After it has eaten up all the food in its territory, it moves to another area. Its two heads do not get along.

name: hydreigon
flavor_text: This brutal PokÃ©mon travels the skies on its six wings. Anything that moves seems like a foe to it, triggering its attack.

name: larvesta
flavor_text: This PokÃ©mon was believed to have been born from the sun. When it evolves, its entire body is engulfed in flames.

name: volcarona
flavor_text: When volcanic ash darkened the atmosphere, it is said that Volcaronaâs fire provided a replacement for the sun.

name: cobalion
flavor_text: This legendary PokÃ©mon battled against humans to protect PokÃ©mon. Its personality is calm and composed.

name: terrakion
flavor_text: This PokÃ©mon came to the defense of PokÃ©mon that had lost their homes in a war among humans.

name: virizion
flavor_text: This PokÃ©mon fought humans in order to protect its friends. Legends about it continue to be passed down.

name: tornadus
flavor_text: The lower half of its body is wrapped in a cloud of energy. It zooms through the sky at 200 mph.

name: thundurus
flavor_text: Countless charred remains mar the landscape of places through which Thundurus has passed.

name: reshiram
flavor_text: This PokÃ©mon appears in legends. It sends flames into the air from its tail, burning up everything around it.

name: zekrom
flavor_text: Concealing itself in lightning clouds, it flies throughout the Unova region. It creates electricity in its tail.

name: landorus
flavor_text: Lands visited by Landorus grant such bountiful crops that it has been hailed as âThe Guardian of the Fields.â

name: kyurem
flavor_text: It generates a powerful, freezing energy inside itself, but its body became frozen when the energy leaked out.

name: keldeo
flavor_text: By blasting water from its hooves, it can glide across water. It excels at using leg moves while battling.

name: meloetta
flavor_text: Its melodies are sung with a special vocalization method that can control the feelings of those who hear it.

name: genesect
flavor_text: Over 300 million years ago, it was feared as the strongest of hunters. It has been modified by Team Plasma.

name: chespin
flavor_text: The quills on its head are usually soft. When it flexes them, the points become so hard and sharp that they can pierce rock.

name: quilladin
flavor_text: It relies on its sturdy shell to deflect predatorsâ attacks. It counterattacks with its sharp quills.

name: chesnaught
flavor_text: Its Tackle is forceful enough to flip a 50-ton tank. It shields its allies from danger with its own body.

name: fennekin
flavor_text: Eating a twig fills it with energy, and its roomy ears give vent to air hotter than 390 degrees Fahrenheit.

name: braixen
flavor_text: It has a twig stuck in its tail. With friction from its tail fur, it sets the twig on fire and launches into battle.

name: delphox
flavor_text: It gazes into the flame at the tip of its branch to achieve a focused state, which allows it to see into the future.

name: froakie
flavor_text: It secretes flexible bubbles from its chest and back. The bubbles reduce the damage it would otherwise take when attacked.

name: frogadier
flavor_text: It can throw bubble-covered pebbles with precise control, hitting empty cans up to a hundred feet away.

name: greninja
flavor_text: It creates throwing stars out of compressed water. When it spins them and throws them at high speed, these stars can split metal in two.

name: bunnelby
flavor_text: They use their large ears to dig burrows. They will dig the whole night through.

name: diggersby
flavor_text: With their powerful ears, they can heft boulders of a ton or more with ease. They can be a big help at construction sites.

name: fletchling
flavor_text: These friendly PokÃ©mon send signals to one another with beautiful chirps and tail-feather movements.

name: fletchinder
flavor_text: From its beak, it expels embers that set the tall grass on fire. Then it pounces on the bewildered prey that pop out of the grass.

name: talonflame
flavor_text: In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.

name: scatterbug
flavor_text: When under attack from bird PokÃ©mon, it spews a poisonous black powder that causes paralysis on contact.

name: spewpa
flavor_text: It lives hidden within thicket shadows. When predators attack, it quickly bristles the fur covering its body in an effort to threaten them.

name: vivillon
flavor_text: Vivillon with many different patterns are found all over the world. These patterns are affected by the climate of their habitat.

name: litleo
flavor_text: The stronger the opponent it faces, the more heat surges from its mane and the more power flows through its body.

name: pyroar
flavor_text: The male with the largest mane of fire is the leader of the pride.

name: flabebe
flavor_text: It draws out and controls the hidden power of flowers. The flower FlabÃ©bÃ© holds is most likely part of its body.

name: floette
flavor_text: It flutters around fields of flowers and cares for flowers that are starting to wilt. It draws out the hidden power of flowers to battle.

name: florges
flavor_text: It claims exquisite flower gardens as its territory, and it obtains power from basking in the energy emitted by flowering plants.

name: skiddo
flavor_text: Thought to be one of the first PokÃ©mon to live in harmony with humans, it has a placid disposition.

name: gogoat
flavor_text: It can tell how its Trainer is feeling by subtle shifts in the grip on its horns. This empathic sense lets them run as if one being.

name: pancham
flavor_text: It does its best to be taken seriously by its enemies, but its glare is not sufficiently intimidating. Chewing on a leaf is its trademark.

name: pangoro
flavor_text: Although it possesses a violent temperament, it wonât put up with bullying. It uses the leaf in its mouth to sense the movements of its enemies.

name: furfrou
flavor_text: Trimming its fluffy fur not only makes it more elegant but also increases the swiftness of its movements.

name: espurr
flavor_text: The organ that emits its intense psychic power is sheltered by its ears to keep power from leaking out.

name: meowstic
flavor_text: When in danger, it raises its ears and releases enough psychic power to grind a 10-ton truck into dust.

name: honedge
flavor_text: Apparently this PokÃ©mon is born when a departed spirit inhabits a sword. It attaches itself to people and drinks their life force.

name: doublade
flavor_text: When Honedge evolves, it divides into two swords, which cooperate via telepathy to coordinate attacks and slash their enemies to ribbons.

name: aegislash
flavor_text: Generations of kings were attended by these PokÃ©mon, which used their spectral power to manipulate and control people and PokÃ©mon.

name: spritzee
flavor_text: It emits a scent that enraptures those who smell it. This fragrance changes depending on what it has eaten.

name: aromatisse
flavor_text: It devises various scents, pleasant and unpleasant, and emits scents that its enemies dislike in order to gain an edge in battle.

name: swirlix
flavor_text: To entangle its opponents in battle, it extrudes white threads as sweet and sticky as cotton candy.

name: slurpuff
flavor_text: It can distinguish the faintest of scents. It puts its sensitive sense of smell to use by helping pastry chefs in their work.

name: inkay
flavor_text: Opponents who stare at the flashing of the light-emitting spots on its body become dazed and lose their will to fight.

name: malamar
flavor_text: It wields the most compelling hypnotic powers of any PokÃ©mon, and it forces others to do whatever it wants.

name: binacle
flavor_text: Two Binacle live together on one rock. When they fight, one of them will move to a different rock.

name: barbaracle
flavor_text: When they evolve, two Binacle multiply into seven. They fight with the power of seven Binacle.

name: skrelp
flavor_text: Camouflaged as rotten kelp, they spray liquid poison on prey that approaches unawares and then finish it off.

name: dragalge
flavor_text: Their poison is strong enough to eat through the hull of a tanker, and they spit it indiscriminately at anything that enters their territory.

name: clauncher
flavor_text: They knock down flying prey by firing compressed water from their massive claws like shooting a pistol.

name: clawitzer
flavor_text: Their enormous claws launch cannonballs of water powerful enough to pierce tanker hulls.

name: helioptile
flavor_text: They make their home in deserts. They can generate their energy from basking in the sun, so eating food is not a requirement.

name: heliolisk
flavor_text: They flare their frills and generate energy. A single Heliolisk can generate sufficient electricity to power a skyscraper.

name: tyrunt
flavor_text: This PokÃ©mon was restored from a fossil. If something happens that it doesnât like, it throws a tantrum and runs wild.

name: tyrantrum
flavor_text: Thanks to its gargantuan jaws, which could shred thick metal plates as if they were paper, it was invincible in the ancient world it once inhabited.

name: amaura
flavor_text: This ancient PokÃ©mon was restored from part of its body that had been frozen in ice for over 100 million years.

name: aurorus
flavor_text: The diamond-shaped crystals on its body expel air as cold as -240 degrees Fahrenheit, surrounding its enemies and encasing them in ice.

name: sylveon
flavor_text: It sends a soothing aura from its ribbonlike feelers to calm fights.

name: hawlucha
flavor_text: Although its body is small, its proficient fighting skills enable it to keep up with big bruisers like Machamp and Hariyama.

name: dedenne
flavor_text: Its whiskers serve as antennas. By sending and receiving electrical waves, it can communicate with others over vast distances.

name: carbink
flavor_text: Born from the temperatures and pressures deep underground, it fires beams from the stone in its head.

name: goomy
flavor_text: The weakest Dragon-type PokÃ©mon, it lives in damp, shady places, so its body doesnât dry out.

name: sliggoo
flavor_text: It drives away opponents by excreting a sticky liquid that can dissolve anything. Its eyes devolved, so it canât see anything.

name: goodra
flavor_text: This very friendly Dragon-type PokÃ©mon will hug its beloved Trainer, leaving that Trainer covered in sticky slime.

name: klefki
flavor_text: These key collectors threaten any attackers by fiercely jingling their keys at them.

name: phantump
flavor_text: These PokÃ©mon are created when spirits possess rotten tree stumps. They prefer to live in abandoned forests.

name: trevenant
flavor_text: It can control trees at will. It will trap people who harm the forest, so they can never leave.

name: pumpkaboo
flavor_text: The pumpkin body is inhabited by a spirit trapped in this world. As the sun sets, it becomes restless and active.

name: gourgeist
flavor_text: Singing in eerie voices, they wander town streets on the night of the new moon. Anyone who hears their song is cursed.

name: bergmite
flavor_text: It blocks opponentsâ attacks with the ice that shields its body. It uses cold air to repair any cracks with new ice.

name: avalugg
flavor_text: Its ice-covered body is as hard as steel. Its cumbersome frame crushes anything that stands in its way.

name: noibat
flavor_text: They live in pitch-black caves. Their enormous ears can emit ultrasonic waves of 200,000 hertz.

name: noivern
flavor_text: They fly around on moonless nights and attack careless prey. Nothing can beat them in a battle in the dark.

name: xerneas
flavor_text: Legends say it can share eternal life. It slept for a thousand years in the form of a tree before its revival.

name: yveltal
flavor_text: When this legendary PokÃ©monâs wings and tail feathers spread wide and glow red, it absorbs the life force of living creatures.

name: zygarde
flavor_text: When the Kalos regionâs ecosystem falls into disarray, it appears and reveals its secret power.

name: diancie
flavor_text: A sudden transformation of Carbink, its pink, glimmering body is said to be the loveliest sight in the whole world.

name: hoopa
flavor_text: This troublemaker sends anything and everything to faraway places using its loop, which can warp space.

name: volcanion
flavor_text: It lets out billows of steam and disappears into the dense fog. Itâs said to live in mountains where humans do not tread.

name: rowlet
flavor_text: This wary PokÃ©mon uses photosynthesis to store up energy during the day, while becoming active at night.

name: dartrix
flavor_text: A bit of a dandy, it spends its free time preening its wings. Its preoccupation with any dirt on its plumage can leave it unable to battle.

name: decidueye
flavor_text: It fires arrow quills from its wings with such precision, they can pierce a pebble at distances over a hundred yards.

name: litten
flavor_text: While grooming itself, it builds up fur inside its stomach. It sets the fur alight and spews fiery attacks, which change based on how it coughs.

name: torracat
flavor_text: At its throat, it bears a bell of fire. The bell rings brightly whenever this PokÃ©mon spits fire.

name: incineroar
flavor_text: This PokÃ©mon has a violent, selfish disposition. If itâs not in the mood to listen, it will ignore its Trainerâs orders with complete nonchalance.

name: popplio
flavor_text: This PokÃ©mon snorts body fluids from its nose, blowing balloons to smash into its foes. Itâs famous for being a hard worker.

name: brionne
flavor_text: A skillful dancer, it creates a sequence of water balloons as it dances, and briskly bombards its enemies.

name: primarina
flavor_text: It controls its water balloons with song. The melody is learned from others of its kind and is passed down from one generation to the next.

name: pikipek
flavor_text: It can peck at a rate of 16 times a second to drill holes in trees. It uses the holes for food storage and for nesting.

name: trumbeak
flavor_text: It eats berries and stores their seeds in its beak. When it encounters enemies or prey, it fires off all the seeds in a burst.

name: toucannon
flavor_text: When it battles, its beak heats up. The temperature can easily exceed 212 degrees Fahrenheit, causing severe burns when it hits.

name: yungoos
flavor_text: With its sharp fangs, it will bite anything. It did not originally live in Alola but was imported from another region.

name: gumshoos
flavor_text: When it finds a trace of its prey, it patiently stakes out the location...but itâs always snoozing by nightfall.

name: grubbin
flavor_text: Its strong jaw enables it to scrape trees and slurp out the sap. It normally lives underground.

name: charjabug
flavor_text: Its body is capable of storing electricity. On camping trips, people are grateful to have one around.

name: vikavolt
flavor_text: It zips around, on sharp lookout for an opening. It concentrates electrical energy within its large jaws and uses it to zap its enemies.

name: crabrawler
flavor_text: While guarding its weak points with its pincers, it looks for an opening and unleashes punches. When it loses, it foams at the mouth and faints.

name: crabominable
flavor_text: It aimed for the top but got lost and ended up on a snowy mountain. Being forced to endure the cold, this PokÃ©mon evolved and grew fur.

name: oricorio
flavor_text: It beats its wings together to create fire. As it moves in the steps of its beautiful dance, it bathes opponents in intense flames.

name: cutiefly
flavor_text: It feeds on the nectar and pollen of flowers. Because itâs able to sense auras, it can identify which flowers are about to bloom.

name: ribombee
flavor_text: It rolls up pollen into puffs. It makes many different varieties, some used as food and others used in battle.

name: rockruff
flavor_text: Itâs considered to be a good PokÃ©mon for beginners because of its friendliness, but its disposition grows rougher as it grows up.

name: lycanroc
flavor_text: Its quick movements confuse its enemies. Well equipped with claws and fangs, it also uses the sharp rocks in its mane as weapons.

name: wishiwashi
flavor_text: When itâs in trouble, its eyes moisten and begin to shine. The shining light attracts its comrades, and they stand together against their enemies.

name: mareanie
flavor_text: It plunges the poison spike on its head into its prey. When the prey has weakened, Mareanie deals the finishing blow with its 10 tentacles.

name: toxapex
flavor_text: Toxapex crawls along the ocean floor on its 12 legs. It leaves a trail of Corsola bits scattered in its wake.

name: mudbray
flavor_text: The mud stuck to Mudbrayâs hooves enhances its grip and its powerful running gait.

name: mudsdale
flavor_text: It spits a mud that provides resistance to both wind and rain, so the walls of old houses were often coated with it.

name: dewpider
flavor_text: It crawls onto the land in search of food. Its water bubble allows it to breathe and protects its soft head.

name: araquanid
flavor_text: It delivers headbutts with the water bubble on its head. Small PokÃ©mon get sucked into the bubble, where they drown.

name: fomantis
flavor_text: During the day, it sleeps and soaks up light. When night falls, it walks around looking for a safer place to sleep.

name: lurantis
flavor_text: It requires a lot of effort to maintain Lurantisâs vivid coloring, but some collectors enjoy this work and treat it as their hobby.

name: morelull
flavor_text: It scatters spores that flicker and glow. Anyone seeing these lights falls into a deep slumber.

name: shiinotic
flavor_text: Forests where Shiinotic live are treacherous to enter at night. People confused by its strange lights can never find their way home again.

name: salandit
flavor_text: It burns its bodily fluids to create a poisonous gas. When its enemies become disoriented from inhaling the gas, it attacks them.

name: salazzle
flavor_text: For some reason, only females have been found. It creates a reverse harem of male Salandit that it lives with.

name: stufful
flavor_text: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.

name: bewear
flavor_text: This immensely dangerous PokÃ©mon possesses overwhelming physical strength. Its habitat is generally off-limits.

name: bounsweet
flavor_text: A delectable aroma pours from its body. They are often swallowed whole by Toucannon lured by that wafting deliciousness.

name: steenee
flavor_text: The sepals on its head developed to protect its body. These are quite hard, so even if pecked by bird PokÃ©mon, this PokÃ©mon is totally fine.

name: tsareena
flavor_text: Its long, striking legs arenât just for show but to be used to kick with skill. In victory, it shows off by kicking the defeated, laughing boisterously.

name: comfey
flavor_text: It attaches flowers to its highly nutritious vine. This revitalizes the flowers, and they give off an aromatic scent.

name: oranguru
flavor_text: Known for its extreme intelligence, this PokÃ©mon will look down on inexperienced Trainers, so itâs best suited to veteran Trainers.

name: passimian
flavor_text: They form groups of roughly 20 individuals. Their mutual bond is remarkableâthey will never let down a comrade.

name: wimpod
flavor_text: This PokÃ©mon is a coward. As it desperately dashes off, the flailing of its many legs leaves a sparkling clean path in its wake.

name: golisopod
flavor_text: With a flashing slash of its giant sharp claws, it cleaves seawaterâor even airâright in two.

name: sandygast
flavor_text: Born from a sand mound playfully built by a child, this PokÃ©mon embodies the grudges of the departed.

name: palossand
flavor_text: Possessed people controlled by this PokÃ©mon transformed its sand mound into a castle. As it evolved, its power to curse grew ever stronger.

name: pyukumuku
flavor_text: Itâs covered in a slime that keeps its skin moist, allowing it to stay on land for days without drying up.

name: type-null
flavor_text: The heavy control mask it wears suppresses its intrinsic capabilities. This PokÃ©mon has some hidden special power.

name: silvally
flavor_text: Its trust in its partner is what awakens it. This PokÃ©mon is capable of changing its type, a flexibility that is well displayed in battle.

name: minior
flavor_text: Originally making its home in the ozone layer, it hurtles to the ground when the shell enclosing its body grows too heavy.

name: komala
flavor_text: It is born asleep, and it dies asleep. All its movements are apparently no more than the results of it tossing and turning in its dreams.

name: turtonator
flavor_text: The shell on its back is chemically unstable and explodes violently if struck. The hole in its stomach is its weak point.

name: togedemaru
flavor_text: The spiny fur on its back is normally at rest. When this PokÃ©mon becomes agitated, its fur stands on end and stabs into its attackers.

name: mimikyu
flavor_text: Its actual appearance is unknown. A scholar who saw what was under its rag was overwhelmed by terror and died from the shock.

name: bruxish
flavor_text: When it unleashes its psychic power from the protuberance on its head, the grating sound of grinding teeth echoes through the area.

name: drampa
flavor_text: It has a compassionate personality, but if it is angered, it completely destroys its surroundings with its intense breath.

name: dhelmise
flavor_text: Swinging its massive anchor, it can KO Wailord in a single blow. What appears to be green seaweed is actually its body.

name: jangmo-o
flavor_text: It expresses its feelings by smacking its scales. Metallic sounds echo through the tall mountains where Jangmo-o lives.

name: hakamo-o
flavor_text: It leaps at its prey with a courageous shout. Its scaly punches tear its opponents to shreds.

name: kommo-o
flavor_text: When it spots enemies, it threatens them by jingling the scales on its tail. Weak opponents will crack and flee in panic.

name: tapu koko
flavor_text: This guardian deity of Melemele is brimming with curiosity. It summons thunderclouds and stores their lightning inside its body.

name: tapu lele
flavor_text: This guardian deity of Akala is guilelessly cruel. The fragrant aroma of flowers is the source of its energy.

name: tapu bulu
flavor_text: It pulls large trees up by the roots and swings them around. It causes vegetation to grow, and then it absorbs energy from the growth.

name: tapu fini
flavor_text: The dense fog it creates brings the downfall and destruction of its confused enemies. Ocean currents are the source of its energy.

name: cosmog
flavor_text: Its body is gaseous and frail. It slowly grows as it collects dust from the atmosphere.

name: cosmoem
flavor_text: Motionless as if dead, its body is faintly warm to the touch. In the distant past, it was called the cocoon of the stars.

name: solgaleo
flavor_text: It is said to live in another world. The intense light it radiates from the surface of its body can make the darkest of nights light up like midday.

name: lunala
flavor_text: It is said to be a female evolution of Cosmog. When its third eye activates, away it flies to another world.

name: nihilego
flavor_text: One of several mysterious Ultra Beasts. People on the street report observing those infested by it suddenly becoming violent.

name: buzzwole
flavor_text: This Ultra Beast appeared from another world. It shows off its body, but whether that display is a boast or a threat remains unclear.

name: pheromosa
flavor_text: One of the dangerous Ultra Beasts, it has been spotted running across the land at terrific speeds.

name: xurkitree
